The Delta variant is causing havoc in South Africa. This highly infectious Delta variant is behind the current surge in new COVID-19 cases. Virologist and Clinical researcher at Numolux Group – Dr. Sanet Aspinal speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa moves to adjusted alert level 4 of the lockdown from Monday morning. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement on Sunday. READ: Delta variant dominating SA third wave The curfew will now begin at 9 pm, ending at 4 am. The country has recorded over 15,000 new COVID-19 cases in the last 24 hours. The NICD said 122 COVID-19 related deaths have also been recorded. eNCA's Shahan Ramkissoon and Faith Mangope speaks to professor Mosa Moshabela from University of KwaZulu-Natal following President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement that the country will move to adjusted alert level 4 on Monday. #DStv403